China is highly concerned about the Palestine-Israel conflict. China condemns any behavior that is harmful to civilians and opposes the escalation of the situation, said Mao Ning, Chinese FM spokesperson. Mao said that the way out of conflict is to resume peace talks, implement the two-state solution and push for a political solution of the Palestine question. China is willing to work with the intl community to find adequate solutions.

The Chinese FM has launched emergency consular protection and assistance for Chinese people in Palestine and Israel, said Chinese FM spokesperson Mao Ning. Chinese nationals should refrain from traveling to Palestine and Israel for the time being, Mao said.
